The paper leverages classification techniques with space transformations and kernel tricks, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the verification of programs and hybrid systems, which falls under the category of formal methods (cs.SC). The paper proposes a counterexample-guided method for synthesizing interpolants, which involves searching for a solution in a space of possible interpolants (cs.PL). The paper also deals with the general quantifier-free theory of nonlinear arithmetic, which is a topic in control theory and systems engineering (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a sound and complete algorithm for synthesizing interpolants, which is a topic in logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO).
